info.name: CalculatedRiskBlog.com
info.description:
2010-06-20 -- Incorporated "Ad Blocking FiltersetP" into the style code.  I previously overlooked the fact that this style is enabled with my Calculated Risk style in my userstyles selections.  Without this code, my Calculated Risk code does not display as intended.  Ooops.  

-- Easier to scan and read, especially the frequent blockquotes in the articles
-- Some ads removed from footer and top of right sidebar

The screenshot below depicts the page rendered with the userstyles code.

style.css:
@namespace url(http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml);

@-moz-document url("http://www.calculatedriskblog.com/") {

/* Calculated Risk */

/* Re-style the font */
body, div{font-family: Corbel, "Trebuchet MS", Helvetica, sans-serif !important;}

div#sidebar-wrap * {font-family: Verdana, sans-serif !important; }

/* Headers  get special treatment */
h1, div#sidebar-wrap h1,
h2, div#sidebar-wrap h2,
h3, div#sidebar-wrap h3,
h4, div#sidebar-wrap h4,
h5, div#sidebar-wrap h5,
h6, div#sidebar-wrap h6 { font-family: Constantia, "Palatino Linotype", "Book Antiqua", Palatino, "Tines New Roman", serif !important; font-weight: normal !important; }

/* Re-style the links */
a {font-weight: normal !important; }
a:visited {color: #B5D171 !important; }
a:hover {color: #cc0000 !important; }

/* Re-style the blockquotes */
 blockquote {
	line-height:inherit !important;
	color: #000 !important;
	background-color: #F2F2FF !important;
	margin: 1em 3em 2em !important;
	padding: 1em !important;
	border: 1px solid #636F7C !important;
      -moz-border-radius : 10px !important;
}

div.post-body img { padding: 2px !important; background-color: #ddd !important; border: 2px solid #c0c0c0 !important;}

div.post-body { line-height: 1.3 !important; }
div#sidebarmid-wrap1 { display:none !important; }



/* Ad Blocking FiltersetP */
/* http://userstyles.org/styles/299 */
